HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 541
By Camper
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Andrew and Rose
Pollard upon the celebration of their sixtieth
wedding anniversary.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in paying tribute
to those successful marriages that have stood the test of time to serve as exemplars for present
and future generations; and
WHEREAS, on March 26, 1965, Andrew Pollard and Rose Marie Briggs were joined in
holy matrimony, and since that fateful day, this outstanding couple has faced the world as one,
basking in the glow of their love for each other during both life's joys and sorrows; and
WHEREAS, Mr. and Mrs. Pollard are highly respected citizens of their community and
the very epitome of good neighbors, as they always endeavor to treat others as they would like
to be treated; and
WHEREAS, the couple owns A & R Barbecue, and Mrs. Pollard is a retired postal clerk
who formerly worked at the Memphis Bulk Mail Center; and
WHEREAS, Andrew and Rose Pollard have both earned the respect of their colleagues
and customers alike for the exemplary quality of their food and service; and
WHEREAS, this fine couple's praiseworthy marriage has produced three children,
Lashun (Gregory) Turner, Brian (Magistrate Judge Mitzi) Pollard, and the late Latrice (Reginald
Sr.) Anthony; and
WHEREAS, the Pollards are also the proud grandparents of Keith (Asia) Pollard,
Brandon Pollard, Randi Anthony, and Reginald Anthony II and the great-grandparents of
Aaliyah Anthony, Kash Pollard, and Major Glass; and
